{
  "texts": [
    "Within the orthodoxy, technology is correspondingly understood as an external closed entity.",
    "By adopting a radically anti-humanistic and operationally constructivist perspective, we can analyze the interactions between technology and science in a way that expands beyond individual human actions and intentions.",
    "This is not a rejection of human rights and dignity or ethics but locates the human subject and individual agency within a dynamic ecology.",
    "Neither does it deny the relevance and importance of authorial authenticity but offers a more dynamic and evolutionary conceptualization of such concepts.",
    "Our approach of autopoiesis and the social system theory facilitates a broader understanding of the role of generative AI within scientific authorship and contributes an explanation of often polarized perceptions of benefits and detriments (see example in Wach et al. 2023)."
  ]
}